      "note": "Sc., \"through our own, actual experience\". This interpolation is based on the reading of the subsequent word as annahu (\"that He is\"), according to the Medina school, in contrast with the more conventional Kufah and Basrah reading innahu (\"verily, He is\"). As Tabari stresses, either of these two readings is correct; I have chosen for my rendering the former inasmuch as it points to the overwhelming, direct insight which will be granted to the blessed on resurrection."
